president bush attacking saddam hussein from 
the campaign trail tuesday said iraqs military must not be 
allowed to benefit frm any humanitarian shipments of food and 
medicine intended for innocent civilians 
he also said there is no reason the persian gulf crisis should 
keep politicians from actively campaigning i am sure every 
democrat agrees we will not allow our political life to be held 
hostage to a crisis bush said 
bush made his comments in gop fundraising events in denver and 
los angeles at the start of a twoday trip on wednesday he will 
campaign in san francisco before returning to washington 
we mean to keep the sanctions in place to keep the pressure 
on and prove to saddam hussein that aggression does not pay 
bush said he said iraqs invasion of kuwait has caused misery 
and suffering for millions 
the chief beneficiaries of bushs visits were rep hank brown 
who is trying to move up to the colorado senate seat being vacated 
by republican sen william armstrong and sen pete wilson in a 
close race for governor in california 
wilsons race is the no 1 target for the gop this year and 
bushs appearances were expected to raise 2 million 
in his speeches bush combined his assault against saddam with 
standard campaign appeals to congress for action on the budget 
deficit anticrime legislation and an overhaul of the clean air 
act 
its time to reach a binding budget agreement that shows the 
american people that we are serious about real deficit reduction 
bush said 
he also called for energy conservation and development of 
alternative fuel sources to curb dependence on foreign oil weve 
indulged a dangerous habit as a nation far too long he said 
despite the partisan nature of his outing bush avoided any 
direct criticism of democrats however democrats seized on the 
occasion to twit bush on allegations that his son neil acted 
improperly in the 1 billion failure of a denver savings and loan 
dick freese chairman of the colorado democratic party issued a 
statement challenging bush to turn over the profits from browns 
fundraiser to the savings and loan bailout 
any good father knows what needs to be done freese said 
when our boys hit a ball through a neighbors window we dont 
make the guy next door pay to fix his own window we get it fixed 
and work with the kids to make good on it 
bush did not comment in his speech on the sampl scandal 
discussing the persian gulf bush raised the possibility that 
humanitarian aid eventually may have to be sent to iraq to offset 
hardships resulting from un sanctions and a blockade on iraqi 
commerce 
should aid become necessary he said it must be 
distributed under strict international supervision to make certain 
that emergency aid reaches those iraqis who need it most 
we cannot allow saddam hussein to divert needed humanitarian 
aid in order to sustain his army of occupation the president 
said 
in a speech in los angeles bush said the gulf crisis requires 
that patriotism take precedence over politics 
so its good that politics stop at the waters edge but that 
still leaves a lot of america in between bush said from long 
beach to long island we should and we will vigorously campaign 
right up to the november election 
for those of us at home he added we can serve our country 
by being the best candidates the best citizens and yes the best 
republicans and democrats we can be 
struggling to maintain a global consensus against iraqs 
aggression bush has kept the persian gulf crisis at the center of 
his public appearances while congress and the public stand united 
behind his policy bush has been expressing concern that the 
support might fade in a prolonged desert showdown with saddam 
never before has the world community been so united bush 
said never since the invasion began has iraq stood so isolated 
and alone the key is collective action sharing the 
responsibilities and the risks the challenges and the costs he 
said more than 20 countries have forces in the gulf 
he said that despite the gulf crisis we can all see the 
outlines emerging of a stronger more peaceful world order 
and let me be clear with all thats at stake the world will 
not allow one dictators aggressive ambitions to stand in the 
way 
flying to denver on air force one bush signed into law a bill 
allowing members of the armed forces in the persian gulf to send 
mail to the united states without cost the law covers the sending 
of letters and recorded tapes 
