<TEXT>
here is a chronology of the events leading up to the indictment 
of charles h keating jr stemming from the collapse of lincoln 
savings and loan 
feb 22 1984 american continental corp formed by phoenix 
millionaire charles h keating jr buys lincoln savings and loan 
for 51 million 
march 12 1986 the federal home loan bank in san francisco 
begins an examination into lincolns rapid growth and investment 
activity 
april 9 1987 sens alan cranston dcalif dennis deconcini 
dariz john glenn dohio and john mccain rariz and donald 
w riegle jr dmich who received large political contributions 
from keating meet with the san francisco examiners 
may 1 1987 san francisco examiners recommend that lincoln be 
seized 
aug 1987 m danny wall bank board chairman orders his staff 
to conduct an independent review of the lincoln examination 
may 20 1988 the bank board in washington signs a memorandum 
providing for a new examination to be conducted by officials in 
washington 
nov 22 1988 the second bank board examination is concluded 
feb 14 1989 the bank board begins a third examination of 
lincoln 
april 13 1989 american continental corp files for protection 
under bankruptcy laws 
april 14 1989 the bank board seizes control of lincoln 
may 12 1989 lincoln alleges that the seizure by regulators 
was illegal 
sept 15 1989 the resolution trust corp seeks 11 billion 
from keating his relatives and associates in a fraud and 
racketeering suit alleging keating diverted depositors money for 
his own use 
nov 17 1989 the senate ethics committee decides to appoint 
an outside counsel to investigate the actions of the five senators 
aug 23 1990 a federal judge upholds the governments 
takeover of lincoln savings and loan 
sept 18 1990 an indictment is unsealed charging keating and 
three others with selling securities by false statements or 
omissions selling securities without qualifications and lying to 
the california department of corporations keating is jailed on 5 
million bail 
</TEXT>
</DOC>

