with the united states 
but cambodia western sahara afghanistan and cyprus remain 
trouble spots and unresolved conflicts 
at a time when the united nations is called upon as never before 
to make peace it remains far in financial arrears largely because 
the united states owes more than 700 million 
for years the united states withheld funds because it said the 
world body was biased against the united states and tilted in favor 
of the soviet union and the third world 
bush has asked the us congress to restore funding however 
