surrounding bombedout buildings and underground bunkers during 
battles around 17th century jaffna fort 
on monday the military evacuated the 200member garrison that 
had defended the fort during a threemonth rebel siege airlifting 
it to medical facilities in outposts in the northern jaffna 
peninsula they left behind 300 other men who had earlier broken 
the rebel siege on the fortress 
a defense ministry communique said 28 men have been killed and 
more than 140 injured since aug 22 when a major operation was 
launched to relieve the government soldiers holed up in the fort 
the latest casualties which occurred monday included a pilot 
whose plane crashed into a lagoon when it failed to pull out of a 
attack dive against a rebel gun position the rebels claimed they 
downed the plane with a sam7 missile 
the officials also said the tigers were using a new incendiary 
mortar shell 
it is a nasty firebomb it explodes and sets everything ablaze 
in a tremendously wide radius when it hits its target said one 
official speaking under standing rules of anonymity 
the military said it has been consolidating positions and 
inching out of the starshaped fortress towards jaffna town across 
a few hundred yards of nomans land 
the tigers say they still have the fort surrounded and have 
beaten back some reinforcements 
the dutch colonial fortress is the only government stronghold in 
the rebelheld town 185 miles northeast of colombo it is the 
political and military base of the rebels who seek a tamil 
homeland independent of the sinhalesedominated government 
in the eastern ampara district police commandos on a search and 
destroy mission shot dead four rebels and discovered a field 
hospital near the kanjimadichiaru village north of ampara town 
the military officials said 
