<TEXT>
a year after a french airliner was blown up over 
the sahara killing 170 people the government stands accused of 
suppressing a report that implicates libya 
the uta dc10 exploded sept 19 1989 over niger en route from 
brazzaville congo to paris the victims included the wife of the 
us ambassador to chad and a chadian cabinet minister 
according to the french news magazine le point investigators 
have determined that three congolese dissidents carried out the 
bombing on the instructions of libyan agents 
french officials have refused to comment on the article or a 
subsequent report in the times of london that said syria as well 
as libya had been implicated 
the times said france is withholding the findings of the 
investigation because it does not want to upset relations with 
libya and syria at this point in the persian gulf crisis set off by 
iraqs takeover of kuwait 
the investigation of the bombing has been headed by judge 
jeanlouis bruguiere one of frances leading experts on 
international terrorism 
