gen merrill a mcpeak tapped to succeed 
fired air force chief of staff michael j dugan is a 
muchdecorated pilot who has flown combat missions in vietnam and 
performed in daring air shows at home 
mcpeak 54 is commander in chief of the pacific air forces at 
hickam air force base in hawaii his responsibility includes us 
air operations over half the globe from japan to the united 
states he commands over 60000 people 
defense secretary dick cheney said monday he would recommend to 
president bush that mcpeak replace dugan whom cheney dismissed for 
revealing to reporters us contingency plans to bomb baghdad and 
iraqi president saddam hussein cheney said dugan a fourstar 
general displayed lack of judgment 
mcpeak entered the air force in 1957 getting his pilot wings a 
year later 
in his 33 years of service mcpeak has flown over 4000 hours on 
fighter planes and also became a skilled parachutist 
for two years starting in 1966 he flew solo or the lead 
position in nearly 200 air shows as a member of the thunderbirds 
the us air force air demonstration squadron 
the stunt flying was good preparation for his next mission 
vietnam 
mcpeak flew 269 combat sorties during the year he served there 
earning several decorations 
he then turned to the academic world completing the national 
war college in 1974 and earning a masters degree at the same time 
mcpeak was assigned to command us air bases in england and 
spain and was promoted to chief of staff of us air forces in 
europe 
he subsequently held several command positions at home assuming 
his current job in july 1988 he was made a full general at the 
same time 
