if the persian gulf crisis culminates with the 
removal of saddam hussein from power experts on that part of the 
world say they wouldnt look for democracy to blossom under the 
iraqi sun saddams most likely successor would be a saddam clone 
the nature of any new government in iraq no matter what the 
denouement of the current crisis is one of the puzzlements for 
those trying to visualize how the crisis might end 
