it is just as likely that he could not survive such a humiliating 
defeat in that event the experts suspect his successor would be 
someone from his inner military circles someone much like him 
in eastern europe in the winter of 1989 and the spring of 1990 
the world saw one autocracy after another fall to be replaced by 
governments responsive to the popular will 
but democracy is alien to iraq and most of the rest of the arab 
world egypt is the only arab country with a semblance of it 
