associated press writerequals 
washington ap president bushs drug advisory council tuesday 
announced a fall conference of civic leaders to discuss strategies 
for winning the fight against illegal drugs in americas cities 
the leadership forum scheduled to be held nov 910 will be 
the basis for organizing a national coalition of the 200 local 
antidrug organizations that have sprung up nationwide the council 
said 
it is based on an emerging belief that a priceless resource in 
our nations war on drugs is a long list of local communities whose 
privatesector leadership is both organized and committed to 
initiate new activities and to strengthen ongoing programs to 
reduce the use of illegal drugs in that community said alvah h 
chapman jr an advisory council member and former chairman of 
knight ridder inc the miamibased newspaper company 
coalitions of local business civic and religious leaders have 
offered advice to schools and private firms about improving drug 
education programs chapman said 
others have launched antidrug advertising campaigns a group in 
santa barbara calif has spurred antidrug peer pressure among 
the citys youth he said still others are fostering programs to 
promote drugfree workplace programs in private businesses 
in miami the coalition that chapman helped found pushed local 
officials to eliminate bureaucratic obstacles to efforts to enforce 
a law that allows demolition of crack houses in that city last 
year 475 crack houses were demolished he said 
the coalition didnt run the bulldozers that knocked down the 
houses but the coalition did use a bulldozer on the bureaucracy 
that was preventing the local law that was in effect from for two 
years from being really applied chapman said 
bush appointed the 27member advisory council to help coordinate 
privatesector and nonprofit drug programs and to help enlist 
volunteer organizations in the war on drugs said the panels 
chairman william moss 
chapman said he hoped that the effort will unleash private money 
to help expand drugtreatment programs which he said must provide 
24hour service to those who want help 
if you are making a decision to kick the drug habit and you 
find the right phone number to call and you decide to call at 505 
on a friday afternoon you most likely get an answering service to 
tell you to call back on monday chapman said 
you can imagine what that does to someone who has reached that 
point of being willing to break with that drug habit chapman 
said 
but chapman said that he was aware of only one community miami 
where such a service is being planned the miami program has not 
been implemented because the local government has yet to help 
finance it chapman said 
