an army medical corpsman but said he will refuse to report on oct 
4 for his basic training 
im not going to show up brown told reporters i dont 
support whats going on i feel the military buildup is 
illadvised he said he was asking the army to let him out of the 
commitment but not filing for conscientious objector status 
patrick colclough 21 of saugerties ny had been a reserve 
officer training corps cadet at st lawrence university in canton 
ny but decided last year to stop participating in training 
ive been soulsearching you might say colclough said 
the recent events really crystallized my opposition to war 
colclough said he faces a hearing sept 26 on his refusal to 
fulfill his rotc contract which could result in an order to active 
duty he said he would ask for conscientious objector status at the 
hearing and refuse to report if ordered to active duty 
