<TEXT>
the 45th un general assembly the first 
of the postcold war era convened tuesday for a threemonth 
session the persian gulf crisis was expected to dominate the 
agenda 
the 159 nations welcomed their newest colleague in the 
international forum liechtenstein which became the 160th member 
when east and west germany unite in october and occupy a single 
seat the membership again will fall to 159 
guido de marco the foreign minister of malta was chosen by 
acclaim president of the general assembly a largely ceremonial 
post but one with influence on the agenda of more than 155 items 
the presidency rotates yearly among regional groupings 
de marco in his inaugural speech called the forthcoming 
unification of germany a sign of new optimism 
he called it a symbol of the new healing role of europe with 
its dismantling of barriers the freeing of peoples the 
reinstating of democratic institutions and the progressive 
abandonment of armaments 
but the president said iraqs aug 2 invasion of kuwait was a 
sign of the dangers ahead he called iraqs attack on its neighbor 
not only an outrageous and illegal action in itself but an 
action which also reflects the bitterness and turmoil the hatred 
and injustice that prevail in the middle east 
de marco told the assembly the world is indeed at a turning 
point in history the question is in which direction are we 
turning 
the security council he said has responded clearly and 
unequivocally in demanding the immediate withdrawal of iraqi forces 
and restoration of the government of kuwait 
we cannot shirk our responsibities he said adding that 
people around the world were looking to the assembly for moral and 
political guidance 
the general assembly cannot adopt legally binding resolutions 
but its statements carry weight as representing the will of the 
international community 
in addition to the persian gulf crisis he said the 
international community faces continuing unsolved conflicts such 
as the status of palestinians many living in the israelioccupied 
west bank and gaza strip 
the palestinian question has a dimension which goes far beyond 
the occupied territories he said it creates rancor 
soulsearching prejudices and unfortunately hatred 
he said convening an international conference on the middle east 
was a fundamental step to peace in the region the current un 
session he said must try to reach a comprehensive settlement of 
the palestinian question 
delay in solving the palestinian issue is a denial to the 
palestinian people of the country which is theirs and to israel of 
those secure and guaranteed frontiers to which it is entitled 
he also cited debt and development poverty terrorism 
narcotics the environment and the role of women as major issues 
confronting the forthcoming general assembly 
