<TEXT>
makers of toothpastes and mouthwashes claiming 
to prevent plaque and other dental conditions must prove their 
products work federal health officials said tuesday 
the food and drug administration told manufacturers to submit 
data supporting their claims within the next six months 
several toothpaste and mouthwash manufacturers have been heavily 
promoting their products ability to reduce or prevent plaque 
tartar and other deposits on teeth and guard against gum disease 
and other dental conditions 
the fda said these statements amount to drug claims because they 
deal with the treatment or prevention of disease and because they 
affect the structure or function of the body 
under the federal food drug and cosmetic act manufacturers 
making drug claims must show that the ingredients in their products 
are safe and effective the agency said 
if the claims cannot be supported with scientific data 
manufacturers would have to remove such claims from the labels of 
their products the fda said 
the american dental association welcomed the fdas action 
its well known that many of these products are effective in 
reducing plaque and problems related to plaque said philip 
weintraub a spokesman for the association 
the association has given its seal of acceptance to several 
toothpaste and mouthwash manufacturers that make antiplaque 
claims he said 
weve looked at their extensive clinical data and determined 
their products are safe and will perform as the manufacturers say 
they will he said 
the fda request for data was to be published in the federal 
register on wednesday 
the agency considered oral healthcare products years earlier in 
its review of nonprescription drugs but much research has been 
conducted since then on plaque and its prevention an fda 
spokeswoman said 
plaque is a thin deposit on teeth that promotes bacteria growth 
studies have implicated plaque in the development of cavities and 
to gingivitis a painful inflammation of the gums 
some manufacturers claim that the abrasives in their toothpaste 
scrapes off plaque some mouth rinses claim to remove plaque 
through antimicrobial or chemical activity 
