<TEXT>
nine european nations called on the un security 
council tuesday to impose an air embargo on iraq and agreed to 
coordinate their air and ground forces in the persian gulf 
defense and foreign ministers of the western european union 
meeting in paris urged the security council to quickly endorse 
closing iraqs air routes to enforce the economic embargo imposed 
after the invasion of kuwait 
the security council has already endorsed the use of naval force 
to back up the embargo 
the decision follows a dramatic rise in tensions between europe 
and iraq following raids last week by iraqi soldiers on the 
diplomatic quarters of at least four nations in kuwait 
the meeting of the western european union follows agreement 
monday by the 12nation european community to expel iraqi military 
aides and restrict movements of iraqs diplomats in their capitals 
the ec also was acting in retaliation for the raids friday on 
the ambassadorial residences or embassies of france belgium and 
canada in kuwait and an earlier raid against the dutch compound 
the troops briefly detained the french military attache and took 
three other french nationals prisoner 
france responded by expelling 29 iraqis proposing to extend the 
un embargo of iraq to air traffic and promising to dispatch 
warplanes tanks helicopters and 4200 soldiers to saudi arabia 
france current president of the western european union called 
tuesdays meeting 
there are currently 28 warships in the gulf region belonging to 
the nine western european union nations but only britain and 
france have committed ground troops in the gulf 
the netherlands offered tuesday to send a squadron of 18 f16 
jet fighters to turkey if the united nations declares an air 
blockade 
france and britain the other western european power with 
significant forces in the region wanted their weu allies to send 
at least token ground troops according to diplomatic sources 
the weu is the sole european body dealing with defense issues 
its members include nine of the 12 european community nations 
neutral ireland greece and denmark are not members 
un diplomats on sunday began drafting a new resolution to 
close iraqs air routes and punish nations flouting the economic 
embargo us officials said 
an air blockade would involve the interception of planes 
approaching iraq and would pose a far greater danger of triggering 
hostilities than the boarding of ships in the persian gulf 
