<TEXT>
a man accused of slaying a leading 
presidential candidate whose death led to a yearold war between 
the government and drug traffickers escaped tuesday from a bogota 
prison police said 
jaime rueda rocha was one of three suspects being held in the 
shooting death of liberal party candidate sen luis carlos galan on 
aug 18 1989 
radio reports said rueda rocha used documents provided by his 
lawyer to persuade prison workers to let him leave the facility 
a police spokeswoman said officials were investigating how rueda 
rocha escaped she confirmed on condition of anonymity that rueda 
rochas lawyer carlos caicedo had been visiting him at the time 
of his escape 
rueda rocha was arrested a month after galans murder the 
government blamed the medellin cocaine cartel for masterminding the 
candidates slaying which led to a major crackdown on drug 
traffickers 
one of the tactics used by the government in its crackdown that 
most angered the drug kingpins was extraditing traffickers wanted 
in the united states on drugrunning and money laundering charges 
the cartel responded with an assassination and bombing campaign 
which in the past year killed about 550 people including three 
presidential candidates during that period the group reportedly 
detonated 300 bombs nationwide 
a domestic airliner also exploded in air shortly after takeoff 
from bogotas airport killing more than 100 people 
on july 27 the medellin cartel declared a unilateral truce in 
its war against the government 
on tuesday a statement signed by cocaine barrons calling 
themselves the extraditables said despite army claims they did 
not intend to resume their bombings of government targets for now 
last weekend the army found 1000 pounds of dynamite in a 
northeastern colombian region where the leader of the medellin 
cartel pablo escobar is said to own vast tracks of land 
