brazil on tuesday scrapped a nuclear 
test site at an air force base deep in the amazonian jungle in a 
ceremony to show the governments peaceful intentions in its 
nuclear program 
president fernando collor de mello acompanied by his three 
military ministers tossed a handful of dirt into a 
1000footdeep concrete and steellined hole that officials said 
was constructed 10 years ago to test bombs it was never used 
the hole was adequate for an eventual nuclear test but this 
will not occur in the brazil of president collor de mello said 
spokesman claudio humberto rosa e silva 
the hole on the serra do cachimbo air force base 930 miles 
northwest of brasilia was excavated in 1979 when brazil was ruled 
by its last military president gen joao figueredo its existence 
was a secret until four years ago even then base officials 
claimed it was used for testing equipment for a brazilian space 
program 
rosa e silva said the hole was secretly constructed by the 
national security council a military agency that has since been 
disbanded 
civilians took the reins of government in 1985 but full 
democracy was not restored until last decembers election victory 
by collor 
the spokesman said collor confirmed the existence of the hole 
last week and decided to go personally to the site to signal his 
position against secret military adventures 
in 1987 brazil developed the means to enrich uranium a crucial 
step towards the construction of nuclear bombs and the country now 
has the capacity to make such weapons according to the brazilian 
society of physics 
historically the countrys nuclear development programs have 
been under control of separate branches of the armed forces 
independent of civilian control 
brazil has refused to sign the 1968 nuclear nonproliferation 
treaty and as a result its nuclear program is not monitored by the 
international agency of atomic energy 
brazilian officials say the treaty is discriminatory because it 
discourages the transfer of nuclear technology to developing 
countries 
last week brazil and argentina the only two latin american 
countries that possess nuclear knowhow released a statement 
promising not to utilize their knowledge to produce atomic wepaons 
