<TEXT>
vienna at the turn of the century was boiling in artistic fever 
among the artists to emerge from that cauldron of creativity was 
egon schiele 
harry n abrams will publish the definitive book on schieles 
work and life in november to coincide with the publication of 
egon schiele the complete works 195 the galerie st 
etienne in new york will mount a special exhibit to celebrate the 
100th anniversary of the austrian expressionist 
with gustav klimt and oskar kokoschka schiele was among the 
most influential artists of that time he was 16 when he was 
admitted to viennas academy of fine arts and by 1910 had already 
developed his style but he enraged a moralistic public with his 
frank treatment of sexual themes 
he died in 1918 a victim of the spanish influenza 
the handsome abrams book contains 94 full color prints and 107 
duotone plates 
here is a list of exhibits and shows at some museums and 
galleries in the united states 
</TEXT>
