the labor department says it is examining 
whether banks that hold securities for pension funds are getting 
proxy ballots to the funds managers in a timely fashion 
assistant labor secretary david george ball said the department 
also will examine whether the proxies absentee ballots for 
shareholders are being delivered to the person responsible at a 
fund for voting them 
shareholders are entitled to a say in the running of a company 
through their vote at annual shareholders meetings proxy ballots 
are sent to those not attending a meeting in person 
like political democracy for corporate democracy to work 
well persons entitled to vote need to be able to get relevant 
information in a timely fashion and to receive their ballots in 
time to cast them ball told a meeting in washington of the 
united shareholders association on monday 
the association is a grassroots organization founded by texas 
oilman t boone pickens in 1986 to fight for shareholder rights 
the group has sponsored numerous proposals at the annual meetings 
of large corporations 
ball said the labor departments office of enforcement will be 
contacting a small sampling of bank trustees to see how they handle 
proxies for pension funds 
he added that if past experience is any indicator i would 
expect that the fact that we are making these inquiries will lead 
to an internal review of procedures by bank trustees to assure 
compliance with the law 
after his speech ball explained that the labor department was 
focusing on banks because banks are the custodians of the large 
pension plans 
he said department statistics show that 90 percent of the 
assets representing 85 percent of plan participants are 
concentrated in just 6 percent of the nations pension plans 
ball said the review to be completed by years end will screen 
200 or 300 banks 
itll be the big ones the ones that are likely to have the 
custodianship of pension plans he said 
the labor department maintains that those who invest the money 
of pension funds have an obligation to manage the assets so they 
retain or increase in value that includes carefully voting their 
proxies 
therefore a fiduciary would be derelict in his or her duty if 
he or she did not vote plan shares on matters which might affect 
the value of shares ball said in his speech 
