<TEXT>
ncr corp said today it would become the first 
computer maker to offer an entire product line from laptop 
computers to giant mainframes based on intel corp microprocessors 
and standardized software 
using the same type of microprocessors the chips that are 
the brains of computers would make the entire line compatible 
meaning a laptop computer could get at information stored on a 
mainframe 
the computer lines of most major makers are divided between 
proprietary or companyspecific processing systems and open 
systems such as those based on intel chips the differences mean 
various computers sold by the same company often are incompatible 
the industry has moved toward open systems in recent years as 
companies want to use the same applications software such as 
spreadsheets or word processing programs on all computers no 
matter what the brand in addition computer users increasingly 
want to connect machines in networks which can be troublesome with 
incompatible models 
ncr though not a major player in generalpurpose computers 
could reap major rewards from its new direction said analysts 
you cant write these guys off as a nonfactor anymore said 
don young of the investment firm sanford c bernstein amp co i 
think its a pretty bold move on their part 
ncr said it eventually would provide computers in seven 
levels or performance and size ranges today it announced six 
machines in three of those levels including workstations and 
servers powerful computers that link networks of lesspowerful 
machines the models released today cost 10000 to 800000 
the higherend models of the new line derive their power by 
linking multiple intel microprocessors in a technique called 
parallel processing ncr says it will power the giant mainframes at 
the top of the line by hooking together thousands of the same chips 
that run tiny laptop computers 
dayton ohiobased ncr long has specialized in computers for 
banks and retail stores and is a major maker of cash registers and 
automated teller machines in recent years it has enjoyed success 
with a line of personal computers built to industry standards using 
intel chips 
it now plans to phase out its old computers and use those 
standards and intel chips on its entire product line 
ncr would become the first company to sell highend mainframe 
computers based on open systems analysts said the models would be 
ncrs entry into the market for extremely powerful computers 
the new strategy will potentially open up their rather narrow 
market into a broad market said rick martin an analyst at 
prudentialbache securities inc the question is can they be one 
of the major players the answer is you just dont know 
in coming weeks ncr also is expected to announce software and 
networking systems that will allow the new computer line to be 
connected throughout a company martin said 
ncrs new direction would be another boon to intel the santa 
clara calif chip company that is enjoying phenomenal success 
its chips are so popular with computer makers that it cant make 
enough to satisfy demand 
but the news could be troubling to motorola inc which makes 
the chips used in some ncr computers ncrs move signals the 
increasing dominanace of intels chips in computers already 
intel chips are the dominant processors in desktop machines 
motorolas microcomputer business is headed for some tough 
times young said 
ncr sells less than 5 billion worth of computers a year out of 
a global market of 200 billion he said by comparison 
international business machines corp the industry leader has 
sales of about 60 billion 
earlier this month ibm announced a new generation of mainframe 
computers based on a proprietary standard ibm also said it plans 
to provide systems that would allow the mainframe computer to 
coordinate corporatewide computing networks 
next month unisys corp the no 3 computer maker also is 
expected to announce products for connecting computers throughout a 
company 
