crucial to us success according to participants in the 
discussions 
egypt has led the way in providing arab troops to the deployment 
in saudi arabia and has lobbied other arab states to isolate iraqs 
saddam hussein eagleburger pointed out 
broomfield said he welcomed those moves and added i am sure 
there are other ways america and other nations can help them 
alleviate some of the economic problems caused by this crisis 
perhaps the debt could be restructured or the united states 
could waive a requirement that all payments be up to date before a 
country can receive new foreign aid he said 
to forgive all the debt however would be a sign that we may 
have lost our senses broomfield said this comes at a time 
when our budget negotiators are figuring out ways to squeeze a few 
more tax dollars out of americas sales clerks and farmers and 
mechanics 
