<TEXT>
general motors corp is free to close plants at 
will but will spend 42 billion to protect the income of employees 
affected by cutbacks under its new labor agreement a newspaper 
said today 
the tentative agreement covering 300000 workers in 29 states 
was reached early monday after 41 hours of nonstop talks between 
the united auto workers and the worlds biggest automaker 
this morning the 300member gm bargaining council met to 
discuss the contract the first step toward submitting the pact to 
the membership 
the meeting was closed but a summary of contract details given 
to group members included wage increases of 3 percent the first 
year and lumpsum payments equal to 3 percent of wages in the 
second and third years and increases in monthly pensions for 
workers with 30 years on the job from 1500 to 1800 
the summary also cited 42 billion in income guarantees and 
indicated that language curbing the companys right to close plants 
was eliminated the detroit free press reported today that the new 
provision in effect gives gm the right to close plants at will 
pete kelly president of local 160 at gms technical center in 
warren mich had some criticism for the settlement but said today 
that he expected it would be overwhelmingly approved 
i think for what general motors got the economic package was 
not sufficient kelly said 
under the pact gm will guarantee workers laid off for up to 12 
weeks in a year 95 percent of their wages by supplementing their 
unemployment benefits the newspaper said anyone laid off for more 
than 12 weeks will be guaranteed full pay for the duration of the 
contract the paper said 
many analysts say gm will have to close at least four assembly 
plants and lay off tens of thousands of people in an industry 
threatened by a sluggish economy and foreign competition 
if the bargaining council approves the agreement it will be put 
to a rankandfile vote to be completed by the end of the month 
were all starving for information over here said joe 
garcia financial secretary for local 645 in van nuys calif 
assembly workers earn 1527 an hor at gm and costofliving 
allowances that carry over from the previous contract would add 
215 an hour by 1993 if inflation runs at 5 percent a year the 
free press said 
the 1987 contract expired at midnight friday and negotiators 
worked under a daybyday extension through the weekend 
the unions contracts cover more than 450000 active workers at 
gm ford motor co and chrysler corp talks between the union and 
ford and chrysler have been on hold while the union concentrates on 
gm hoping to use the pact reached there as a pattern for 
agreements with the other automakers 
