trading was suspended today at the chicago board 
of trade after an electrical problem knocked out power to most of 
the 40story downtown building officials said 
the power failure hit about two hours before the first trading 
of the day was scheduled to begin at 720 am cdt in financial 
contracts such as treasury bonds said frederick grede the 
exchanges vice president of administration 
most of the buildings electrical systems were knocked out of 
commission including electronic trading mechanisms phones and 
elevators grede said power also was out on the buildings fourth 
floor where the trading pits are located he said 
although few people were in the building initially employees 
and traders began arriving for work a short time later and scores 
of them waited in the lobby rather than attempting to climb the 
stairs to their offices he said 
