<TEXT>
computer pioneer steve jobs unveiled four 
new products today that he hopes will salvage his new company next 
computer inc 
the products included a more powerful colorscreen version of 
the next computer as well as an entrylevel under5000 model 
half the cost of the current machine 
jobs said the company already has received orders for more than 
15000 of the new products 
in addition lotus development corp creator of the popular 
123 spreadsheet announced a new spreadsheet for the next 
computer called lotus improv 
the product provides a new approach to spreadsheets by enabling 
users to click a mouse to view information the software designed 
specifically for the next computer uses plain english formulas 
many other software developers were expected to announce new 
applications programs for the next throughout the allday news 
conference 
the new products were designed to answer critics who say the 
next is too expensive too slow in need of a color monitor and 
lacking imaginative software that would give people a compelling 
reason to buy it 
the next machine was supposed to revolutionize personal 
computers much as did the apple computer invented by jobs and 
steve wozniak in 1976 and jobs later macintosh 
to store data the next uses a removable optical disc which 
provides far greater capacity than the magnetic floppy discs found 
on most personal computers it also can reproduce sharp graphics 
and has a builtin system that makes it easier for software 
developers to write new programs 
while next has been praised for these hightech innovations 
only several thousand of the machines have been sold and next has 
failed to generate great interest among breadandbutter corporate 
computer users analysts say 
businessland a computer store chain that signed an exclusive 
deal with next in march 1989 to sell its machines domestically to 
corporations had predicted sales would hit 100 million in the 
first year 
but international data corp a hightech research firm 
estimates that fewer than 7000 nexts were sold as of june 
at less than 5000 the price tag makes the new machines 
competitive with both the highend personal computers of apple 
computer inc and international business machines corp and the 
lowend workstations of companies like sun microsstems inc 
next which is privately held does not disclose its sales or 
finances 
despite its sluggish start no one is predicting nexts demise 
the company is heavily capitalized and one of its principal 
owners the japanese hightech company canon inc paid 100 
million for a onesixth share last year 
jobs founded next in 1985 after leaving apple in a dispute 
