disappointments said michael metz chief market analyst at 
oppenheimer amp co the question is whether the fed opts to fight 
inflation or fight a recession 
the federal reserve board is widely believed to be weighing the 
need to pump life into the economy by lowering interest rates 
the central bank has indicated it would be inclined to relax its 
monetary policy if white house and congressional negotiators agree 
on ways to trim the budget deficit but inflation considerations 
might stay the feds hand especially if the middle east crisis 
drags on and keeps oil prices rising 
