soybean futures prices rose moderately tuesday on 
the chicago board of trade recovering most of the ground lost in 
the previous session amid talk of possible frost in the midwest 
early next week 
most corn futures also advanced but wheat futures retreated 
slightly 
victor lespinasse an assistant vice president for grain trading 
with dean witter reynolds inc said some private forecasters 
predicted frost in the midwest by monday fueling fears of damage 
to the slowly maturing soybean and corn crops 
a weekly government report on monday showed leaves dropping in 
22 percent of the soybean crop as of sunday compared with an 
average of 39 percent for that date 
thirtythree percent of the corn crop was in the mature stage as 
of sunday compared with the average pace of 61 percent according 
to the agriculture department report 
even before frost entered the forecasts traders were concerned 
that the current spate of cool rainy weather in the midwest would 
continue to slow crop development 
