gulf crisis should not be allowed to derail an international 
freetrade accord due to be reached this december 
the message we wish to pass to everyone is that this crisis 
cannot have a protectionist response italys foreign trade 
minister renato ruggiero said 
the foreign trade ministers of the 12 ec members met to discuss 
the latest round of trade liberalization talks the talks is being 
held under the auspices of the general agreement on tariffs and 
trade 
the 105nation negotiations are blocked mainly because of 
disagreement between the united states and the ec over farm 
supports 
ec members fear that some countries will be reluctant to commit 
themselves to strict trade agreements when their economies are 
suffering from higher oil prices due to the crisis prompted by 
iraqs aug 2 invasion of kuwait 
to resolve the problem the ec ministers discussed providing 
greater access to the markets of industrialized countries for 
textiles a major product of the developing world 
