<TEXT>
ncr corp said tuesday it would replace its 
entire computer line with industrystandard machines that all could 
communicate with each other a first for an oldline computer 
maker 
the new models from a company better known for its cash 
registers and automated teller machines could strenghten ncrs 
presence in the computer industry where it has only done well 
among retailing and banking customers analysts said 
what we are about to see is whether a standard opensystems 
product line can get them into the mainstream or not said rick 
martin who follows computers for prudentialbache securities inc 
ncr said it would produce the entire computer line from tiny 
laptop models to extremely powerful mainframes from the same intel 
corp computer chips that would make ncr the first company to use 
the same microprocessor for a product line this broad analysts 
said 
using the same microprocessor the computeronachip that is 
the brain of modern computers would make the line compatible 
meaning a laptop could get at information stored on a mainframe 
ncr also said the computers would run industrystandard 
operating systems which control a computers internal functions 
the computer lines of most major makers including ncr are 
divided between proprietary or companyspecific processing 
systems and open or industrystandard systems that means 
various models sold by the same company often are incompatible 
applications software such as database or wordprocessing 
programs must be tailored to a specific operating system if the 
software is designed for a proprietary system it cant be used on 
any other type of computer 
but corporations increasingly want to be able to use the same 
applications software on all their machines and to connect 
computers in networks which can be troublesome with incompatible 
models 
ncr executives speaking at a new york news conference said 
their new line would address those concerns 
the dayton ohiobased company said it eventually would provide 
computers in seven levels or ranges of performance and size 
on tuesday it announced six machines in three levels ranging from 
desktop workstatons to mainframeclass machines priced from 
10000 to 800000 
the higherend models of the new line derive their power by 
linking multiple intel microprocessors in an emerging technique 
called parallel processing 
ncr said it will power the models planned for the top of the 
line by hooking together thousands of microprocessors however ncr 
didnt say when those models would be available 
ncr said the most powerful model will process more than 100000 
million instructions per second or mips a standard measure of 
computing speed by contrast ibms new topoftheline model 
announced earlier this month will operate at about 230 mips 
analysts say 
but operating systems and applications software need to be 
developed to exploit the parallelprocessing technology analysts 
say software used for standard mainframes which have up to eight 
processors would not run on machines with thousands of processors 
in related news tuesday the unix development unit of american 
telephone amp telegraph co said would modify the unix operating 
system for use on multipleprocessor computers unix was created by 
atampt 
in coming weeks ncr said it will announce software and 
networking systems that will allow the new computer line to be 
connected throughout a company 
ncr sells less than 5 billion worth of computers a year out of 
a global market of 200 billion according to the investment firm 
sanford c bernstein amp co by comparison ibm the industry leader 
has sales of about 60 billion 
</TEXT>
