<TEXT>
the government securities subsidiary of 
stotler group inc has lost its registration with the securities 
and exchange commission as part of a settlement of regulatory 
charges the sec announced tuesday 
without admitting or denying wrongdoing stotler and co the 
affiliate of the troubled chicago futures concern settled an sec 
administrative action brought last month 
as a result stotlers sec registration as a government 
securities broker dealer was revoked 
stotler and co which was also a major futures brokerage until 
earlier this summer when it ran into money and legal problems 
settled a similar administrative action with federal futures 
regulators 
the commodity futures trading commission still has a civil 
lawsuit pending against another stotler subsidiary stotler funds 
inc that alleges misuse of 5 million in customer funds 
stotler group and stotler and co last month filed for 
liquidation under federal bankruptcy law 
stotler group was headed by former chicago board of trade 
chairman karsten cash mahlmann until a day after the cftc sued 
alleged misuse of customer funds mahlmann who resigned as head of 
the worlds largest futures exchange the same day has not been 
accused of any illegal activity 
the sec began administrative proceedings aug 21 against stotler 
and co charging the concern with violating regulations concerning 
the sale of government securities 
the sec accused stotler and co of selling or trying to sell 
government securities since november 1988 without being a member of 
a registered securities association such as the national 
association of securities dealers 
the sec also accused stotler of failing to maintain a minimum 
amount of cash and assets to offset risks the socalled net 
capital requirement stotler and co also was accused of not 
keeping proper records including filing financial reports with the 
sec 
ron peterson a chicago lawyer appointed trustee of stotler and 
co by the bankruptcy court did not immediately return a telephone 
call tuesday seeking comment 
