united mine workers president richard 
trumka rebuffed in efforts to merge with the main oil industry 
union said tuesday a national energy union is the only way to win 
concessions from big business 
trumka addressing the umws 100th anniversary convention said 
only a unified labor organization can combat multinational oil and 
coal conglomerates with diversified interests 
he said it unions had to do what we must to challenge those 
corporate goliaths on their own turf not only as the union of the 
coal fields but as the union of energy workers 
dividing workers in oil coal power and petrochemical 
industries is the modern equivalent of craft unionism trumka 
said referring to the policy of having a separate union for every 
task at a job site 
at its 1986 convention the umw gave its governing body the 
international executive board authority to seek a merger with 
other energy unions a proposed merger with the oil chemical and 
atomic workers however collapsed in 1987 when the ocaws board 
balked at the proposal 
talks between the unions later resumed but the two sides were 
unable to reach an agreement before the coal miners convention 
began monday 
also tuesday the umws chief financial officer asked the 1000 
convention delegates for permission to use interest from a strike 
fund to pay legal advertising and negotiating costs associated 
with strikes 
the strike fund at 574 million as of aug 31 was set up 
during the 1983 convention but it was limited to paying strike 
benefits directly to miners 
umw secretarytreasurer john banovic said those pay and health 
benefits totaled 5 million during 1989 including payments to 
workers during the 10month strike against the pittston co in west 
virginia virginia and kentucky that ended last february but he 
said the total cost of strikes in 1989 was 60 million to 70 
million 
in addition the union faces 52 million in fines levied by a 
virginia judge for pittstonrelated strike activities banovic said 
the strike fund generates about 4 million a year at current 
interest rates 
delegates are to vote later on that proposal plus another that 
would give the unions international executive board authority to 
close or merge some of the 21 union districts in the united states 
and canada 
