in them reiner said he declined to describe in detail how the 
bonds were misrepresented 
asked what happened to the investors money reiner said the 
money was transferred to american continental and from there to mr 
keating 
the department of corporations has already sued keating on 
behalf of the investors however the bondholders themselves at one 
point filed a claim against the department saying it should never 
have allowed the bonds to be sold in the lincoln branches because 
they constituted an extreme risk to the investing public 
