<TEXT>
a connecticutbased satellite company said 
tuesday it would appeal a federal courts dismissal of the firms 
15 billion antitrust suit against comsat corp 
pan american satellite said the suit was dismissed thursday in 
us district court in manhattan on grounds that comsat a 
congressionally created corporation was immune from such antitrust 
suits 
rene anselmo the chairman of pan american said its just a 
question of law i would expect we would prevail on appeal 
pan american based in greenwich conn filed suit in july 
1989 charging comsat with fixing prices and blocking competition 
for international satellite communications services 
comsat which stands for communications satellite corp sells 
to us companies access to intelsat the 117nation consortium of 
satellite telecommunications users 
pan american satellite is the first privately owned 
international satellite communications company 
anselmo established pan american in 1984 after thenpresident 
reagan signed a presidential determination that it would be in the 
national interest to allow socalled alternative satellite systems 
such as pas to compete with comsat and intelsat 
pan american launched its pas1 satellite in june 1988 and began 
service in september to latin america and europe 
congress created comsat in the communications satellite act of 
1962 comsat is a private publicly traded company that leases 
intelsat circuits to companies such as american telephone amp 
telegraph co mci us sprint and television networks 
pan americans suit sought 500 million in actual damages which 
would be tripled under federal law and a permanent injunction 
enjoining comsat from engaging in alleged illegal activities 
</TEXT>
</DOC>

